WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:53.510
Somewhere in the North Blue,

3
00:01:51.050 --> 00:01:56.010
North Blue
The Kingdom of Lvneel

4
00:01:53.510 --> 00:01:56.010
there was a man named
Mont Blanc Noland.

5
00:01:56.050 --> 00:02:04.270
Raigo

6
00:01:57.640 --> 00:02:03.560
Noland was an explorer who always
spoke of his fantastical adventures.

7
00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:09.900
But the villagers could never
tell if they were true or not.

8
00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:15.870
One day, Noland returned from
a journey and reported to the king.

9
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:19.540
It stands all the more proudly
and beautifully in ruin!

10
00:02:20.330 --> 00:02:22.040
The city's name is Shandora!

11
00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:26.000
It's the very definition
of "City of Gold."

12
00:02:27.460 --> 00:02:30.460
Five Years Later

13
00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:33.470
Mary Geoise has finally granted us
permission to enter the Grand Line.

14
00:02:33.930 --> 00:02:37.100
As such, I wish to send you
on another mission.

15
00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:38.810
It would be my pleasure!

16
00:02:38.810 --> 00:02:45.600
However, I've decided that my soldiers
and I will join you on this journey.

17
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:46.900
Understood?

18
00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:47.900
Yes!

19
00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.940
One Year Before Noland's Arrival

20
00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:52.400
Kalgara!

21
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:53.400
Seto...

22
00:02:53.400 --> 00:02:55.280
You're off to ring the bell, right?

23
00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:56.820
I'll help.

24
00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.370
Hey, Nola.

25
00:03:01.370 --> 00:03:03.710
You sure are getting cozy
in these ruins.

26
00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:09.960
Say! When do you suppose
Noland and his crew will return?

27
00:03:11.130 --> 00:03:13.970
You ask that every time
you come here.

28
00:03:14.380 --> 00:03:16.930
It won't be so easy
for him to come back.

29
00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:20.300
He was born in the far northern seas.

30
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:22.310
He also has a family back home.

31
00:03:22.310 --> 00:03:24.180
But he did promise.

32
00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:29.690
As long as we keep ringing this bell,
he'll show up sooner or later.

33
00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:35.110
What is this?!

34
00:03:35.110 --> 00:03:36.200
This looks bad!

35
00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:38.990
Come, Seto! Protect the village!

36
00:03:57.010 --> 00:04:02.430
November 16, 1127
The Pelagic Calendar

37
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:03.640
Why?!

38
00:04:05.270 --> 00:04:07.810
Why does the island
suddenly end here?!

39
00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:12.480
Why, you...!

40
00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:14.780
You lied to me!

41
00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:18.240
Where is this gold of yours?!

42
00:04:18.740 --> 00:04:20.530
Where did the village go?!

43
00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:23.950
What happened to this island?!

44
00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:25.370
Kalgara!

45
00:04:25.370 --> 00:04:27.580
If you're alive, let me hear it!

46
00:04:27.580 --> 00:04:29.460
The sound of the gold bell!

47
00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:32.630
Answer me, Light of Shandora!

48
00:04:35.510 --> 00:04:39.010
The Kingdom of Lvneel

49
00:04:36.340 --> 00:04:39.010
Noland's public execution
is about to start!

50
00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.220
Hey! This way, guys!

51
00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:44.180
Six years ago,

52
00:04:44.180 --> 00:04:48.480
I saw a giant city of gold
on the Grand Line island of Jaya!

53
00:04:49.190 --> 00:04:52.310
The City of Gold exists! I swear it!

54
00:04:52.650 --> 00:04:55.690
Then let's hear from
one of your crewmen.

55
00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:58.740
Is this man telling the truth?

56
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:01.530
No. It's a total lie.

57
00:05:01.990 --> 00:05:05.700
What?! Noland is a liar?!

58
00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:08.160
Then... all his stories were fake?!

59
00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:09.410
That's messed up!

60
00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:12.040
He lied to the whole kingdom
and acted like a hero!

61
00:05:12.920 --> 00:05:16.300
Who is that witness?!
He's not part of our crew!

62
00:05:16.300 --> 00:05:18.210
Did you see Kalgara
and the villagers?!

63
00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:21.050
Commodore! What
happened out there?!

64
00:05:21.430 --> 00:05:22.800
Seize them!

65
00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:25.760
Dammit!

66
00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:27.810
You guys...

67
00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:33.560
For his heinous lies,

68
00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:37.070
Mont Blanc Noland is hereby
sentenced to death by beheading!

69
00:05:38.690 --> 00:05:40.030
Liar!

70
00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:43.530
– He's a liar!
– Liar!

71
00:05:43.530 --> 00:05:46.410
The commodore would never lie!

72
00:05:46.410 --> 00:05:47.790
Commodore!

73
00:05:47.790 --> 00:06:00.670
– Liar! Liar!
– Liar! Liar!

74
00:06:43.090 --> 00:06:46.260
God! It's a giant island of vearth!

75
00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:48.760
Indeed. Did you hear it?

76
00:06:48.760 --> 00:06:51.470
That is the singing voice
of this glorious vearth...

77
00:06:51.470 --> 00:06:54.940
This truly is the birth of a holy land.

78
00:06:55.310 --> 00:06:58.020
That is where I must live!

79
00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:03.690
What happened?!

80
00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:07.370
What's going on?!
I can barely breathe!

81
00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:08.950
Is everyone all right?!

82
00:07:08.950 --> 00:07:10.530
Pull yourselves together!

83
00:07:10.530 --> 00:07:11.740
Snap out of it!

84
00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:13.750
Tend to the wounded! Hurry!

85
00:07:13.750 --> 00:07:16.420
Kalgara! Intruders!

86
00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:19.420
I hereby claim this vearth as my own!

87
00:07:19.420 --> 00:07:21.420
I am God!

88
00:07:23.050 --> 00:07:24.920
God, my ass!

89
00:07:24.920 --> 00:07:27.800
Hold them back, warriors!

90
00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:30.260
We cannot let this
land be taken from us!

91
00:07:32.970 --> 00:07:35.850
We made a promise, Noland...

92
00:07:35.850 --> 00:07:39.110
that we would meet again someday...

93
00:07:39.560 --> 00:07:40.980
Kalgara...

94
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:43.320
Where did you go?!

95
00:07:43.320 --> 00:07:49.030
When you return to Jaya, what will
you think when you see we've gone?

96
00:07:50.030 --> 00:07:51.620
Hold on a little longer!

97
00:07:51.620 --> 00:07:53.620
I'll send a message that...

98
00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:56.290
we are here!

99
00:07:56.290 --> 00:07:58.790
Are you alive?!

100
00:07:58.790 --> 00:08:01.540
I have so much to tell you...

101
00:08:02.670 --> 00:08:03.840
Kalgara...

102
00:08:04.590 --> 00:08:08.260
I just want to know if you're okay...

103
00:08:09.390 --> 00:08:13.760
Let's meet on this very land
again someday, Noland!

104
00:08:14.810 --> 00:08:18.060
Shine the Light of Shandora!

105
00:08:18.890 --> 00:08:22.230
Great Warrior Kalgara
continued to shout.

106
00:08:22.230 --> 00:08:24.570
Just once would've been enough...

107
00:08:25.110 --> 00:08:31.950
for he believed the Light of Shandora
would echo and let everyone know:

108
00:08:31.950 --> 00:08:34.410
We are here!

109
00:08:34.410 --> 00:08:38.040
However, the bell never once rang out.

110
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:44.460
Later, Blue Sea sailors came to
the village and told us everything.

111
00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:48.590
Noland, to whom we owe
so much, died branded a liar...

112
00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:55.220
all because he had such pride in our city
that he refused to deny Shandora's existence!

113
00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:58.480
But it was already too late,

114
00:08:58.480 --> 00:09:04.070
for Great Warrior Kalgara had died
honorably in battle here in the sky...

115
00:09:04.520 --> 00:09:07.150
never being able
to convey his message...

116
00:09:07.150 --> 00:09:07.990
That...

117
00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:11.610
is Great Warrior Kalgara's regret.

118
00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:13.660
Do you think it could still reach him?

119
00:09:13.660 --> 00:09:15.490
That bell!

120
00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:18.660
If we rang it now,
would its sound reach Noland?!

121
00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:22.460
That's a good question...

122
00:09:22.830 --> 00:09:25.500
We are close to heaven here...

123
00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:31.880
Wyper! We'll die if we don't run now!

124
00:09:32.260 --> 00:09:33.340
Come on!

125
00:09:34.550 --> 00:09:36.390
Wyper...

126
00:09:36.390 --> 00:09:37.350
Enel...

127
00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:41.770
What gives you the right
to take everything away?!

128
00:09:45.940 --> 00:09:48.690
This is the sky! God's domain!

129
00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:51.360
Everything is a blight!

130
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:55.660
The people, the trees, the land!
Return to where you belong!

131
00:09:55.660 --> 00:09:58.990
Let it all rain into the Blue Sea!

132
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:04.040
Hurry!

133
00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:06.130
Angel Island won't last much longer!

134
00:10:07.920 --> 00:10:09.840
There are lots of injured people!

135
00:10:09.840 --> 00:10:12.090
Get them on a boat
and give them first aid!

136
00:10:12.930 --> 00:10:13.800
Run!

137
00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:15.970
– Hurry!
– Hurry, get to sea!

138
00:10:18.890 --> 00:10:22.690
If that girl's speech had been
even a moment later...

139
00:10:22.690 --> 00:10:24.440
Is she all right?!

140
00:10:37.030 --> 00:10:42.750
Look how the angels scurry about
like a line of disturbed ants!

141
00:10:42.750 --> 00:10:47.290
Return to your proper form, Skypiea!

142
00:10:49.710 --> 00:10:51.050
What is that?!

143
00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:54.010
A hole in the White-White Sea?!

144
00:10:54.010 --> 00:10:58.350
I have no need for this
sentimental old temple either!

145
00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:06.350
Nor for the city of Shandora below it!

146
00:11:16.280 --> 00:11:21.040
There is but one thing left
in this land that I desire!

147
00:11:21.040 --> 00:11:23.910
The grand golden bell!

148
00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:28.210
Even now, there are still two voices?

149
00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:30.960
Geez! How can he run so fast?!

150
00:11:31.710 --> 00:11:33.800
Nami! You better be alright!

151
00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:38.640
I won't let you have
that golden bell, Enel!

152
00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:53.730
What is it that Enel wants up there?

153
00:11:53.730 --> 00:11:55.860
A golden bell at the very top.

154
00:11:56.280 --> 00:11:57.450
A bell...

155
00:11:57.910 --> 00:11:59.700
A golden bell?

156
00:12:00.910 --> 00:12:03.410
That's what you said earlier, right?

157
00:12:03.410 --> 00:12:04.500
Wyper...

158
00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:05.500
Yes...

159
00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:08.830
Wh-Wh-What're you guys
talking about?!

160
00:12:09.330 --> 00:12:15.210
You also spoke of the bell before
Enel electrocuted you.

161
00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:17.300
So that's what he's after?

162
00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:19.550
Where exactly is it?!

163
00:12:19.550 --> 00:12:21.550
Hey! Wait!

164
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:23.810
There's no time for that!

165
00:12:23.810 --> 00:12:25.270
You saw that thunderbolt!

166
00:12:26.020 --> 00:12:28.390
We're gonna die if we
don't get outta here!

167
00:12:30.980 --> 00:12:34.070
It's somewhere near
the top of this giant vine.

168
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:36.690
How?! How do you know that?!

169
00:12:36.690 --> 00:12:37.740
Hey!

170
00:12:38.700 --> 00:12:41.910
We promised we'd wait
for Nami back on the ship!

171
00:12:42.410 --> 00:12:46.160
She'll be back with
Luffy any minute now!

172
00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:47.660
He's right, Wyper!

173
00:12:48.790 --> 00:12:51.920
The ruins of Shandora
in the layer beneath us...

174
00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:55.960
This vine pierces through
the very center of the city.

175
00:12:57.010 --> 00:12:59.630
Hey! Look!

176
00:12:59.630 --> 00:13:03.470
Ruins or not, it's been
blasted to pieces!

177
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:08.270
And we could be next, you know!

178
00:13:08.270 --> 00:13:13.860
I found a map in the ruins
which suggested the grand bell tower

179
00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:16.530
once stood in the city's center.

180
00:13:16.900 --> 00:13:20.490
In other words, the shock from
being thrust upward by the vine

181
00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:23.370
might have thrown the
bell even further skyward.

182
00:13:38.510 --> 00:13:39.800
Hey, guys!

183
00:13:44.180 --> 00:13:48.270
There's a huge bell
in the City of Gold, right?

184
00:13:54.650 --> 00:13:57.610
Now, then. I have
risen above Giant Jack.

185
00:13:58.480 --> 00:14:04.780
I doubt anyone would search
the skies above God's Shrine.

186
00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:07.990
Even after 400 years...

187
00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:11.370
Now, then. Where could it be?

188
00:14:11.870 --> 00:14:13.830
Where is the golden bell...?

189
00:14:26.970 --> 00:14:28.430
What is this place?!

190
00:14:34.650 --> 00:14:36.520
Him again...

191
00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:40.280
I'm astonished he made it here
with that weight attached.

192
00:14:42.110 --> 00:14:43.780
There you are!

193
00:14:44.570 --> 00:14:49.660
Wait right there! Enel!

194
00:14:50.450 --> 00:14:52.120
Such a pest.

195
00:15:16.060 --> 00:15:18.270
Wyper! What are you trying to do?!

196
00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:20.770
Don't tell me you're
gonna climb the vine?!

197
00:15:25.740 --> 00:15:28.030
Everyone! Get away from the vine!

198
00:15:28.030 --> 00:15:29.910
Something's falling!

199
00:15:37.880 --> 00:15:38.880
The tip of the vine?!

200
00:15:39.250 --> 00:15:40.460
What happened up there?!

201
00:15:40.460 --> 00:15:44.880
Hey, now! Don't tell me
Luffy and Nami fell with it?!

202
00:15:44.880 --> 00:15:46.260
Wyper!

203
00:15:47.180 --> 00:15:50.850
Stop it! You can't go like this!

204
00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:52.600
You're all beat up!

205
00:15:52.600 --> 00:15:57.690
And even if you do climb up there,
you have no way to reach Enel!

206
00:15:57.690 --> 00:15:58.480
It's...

207
00:15:59.730 --> 00:16:01.860
It's right above us!

208
00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:08.070
The bell that Great Warrior Kalgara sought!

209
00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:21.630
How do you intend to climb
up here in that state?

210
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:24.510
D-Damn you!

211
00:16:27.260 --> 00:16:29.840
Stay there for a while.

212
00:16:30.760 --> 00:16:33.260
I'll show you something interesting.

213
00:16:42.610 --> 00:16:43.690
Huh?

214
00:16:46.650 --> 00:16:50.450
Oh, right! I gotta figure
this out while he's gone!

215
00:17:06.130 --> 00:17:10.630
Gum-Gum...

216
00:17:12.010 --> 00:17:14.720
Yo-Yo!

217
00:17:21.480 --> 00:17:23.110
What is he doing?!

218
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:31.820
Alright! I'm back on track!

219
00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:34.870
Now's my chance to get on board!

220
00:17:38.830 --> 00:17:40.750
Luffy! I finally caught up to you!

221
00:17:40.750 --> 00:17:43.580
Huh? Nami! What're you doing here?!

222
00:17:43.960 --> 00:17:45.880
I came to get you!

223
00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:49.630
I got down safely
thanks to Sanji and Usopp!

224
00:17:50.920 --> 00:17:53.430
Really?! You did?!

225
00:17:53.430 --> 00:17:54.470
That's great!

226
00:17:54.970 --> 00:17:56.510
But more importantly...

227
00:17:57.180 --> 00:17:57.970
Wait!

228
00:17:59.220 --> 00:18:00.390
What's that?!

229
00:18:04.690 --> 00:18:08.280
The thunderclouds are
changing shape!

230
00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:14.360
Up in the sky!

231
00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:16.330
Help!

232
00:18:16.330 --> 00:18:19.540
– The sky's pitch dark!
– This is bad! Save us!

233
00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:21.460
– Mom!
– What's happening?!

234
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.920
To the sea! Quickly!

235
00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:29.250
There's a giant ball floating in the sky!

236
00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:35.800
That thing's bad news...

237
00:18:36.300 --> 00:18:40.180
That's a thundercloud wrapped
in a spherical shroud...

238
00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:44.560
packed with intense currents
and electric discharges!

239
00:18:57.370 --> 00:19:00.410
It's directly above Angel Island!

240
00:19:01.660 --> 00:19:03.660
The thunderclouds turned spherical...

241
00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:06.960
Th-This has to be a nightmare!

242
00:19:06.960 --> 00:19:08.880
There's no way this can be real!

243
00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:15.180
What more is he
planning to unleash?!

244
00:19:21.140 --> 00:19:23.230
The sea! To the sea, quickly!

245
00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:24.350
Wait!

246
00:19:32.610 --> 00:19:36.030
It's time for you to learn that
the heavens belong to me!

247
00:19:38.160 --> 00:19:42.540
Only with the Ark Maxim
and my divine might

248
00:19:42.540 --> 00:19:45.210
can I accomplish such godly acts!

249
00:19:46.420 --> 00:19:47.670
Look at that!

250
00:19:47.670 --> 00:19:49.580
It's falling onto Angel Island!

251
00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:52.420
It's too late!

252
00:19:52.420 --> 00:19:54.340
We're not going to make it!

253
00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:55.840
Run! Hurry!

254
00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:57.340
I'm scared!

255
00:20:05.930 --> 00:20:07.640
Raigo.

256
00:20:35.130 --> 00:20:37.130
No, this can't be real!

257
00:20:37.130 --> 00:20:39.430
Did the White Berets escape too?

258
00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:42.510
They saved us...

259
00:20:42.510 --> 00:20:44.310
The island where we were born...

260
00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:48.270
Our hometown...
They're completely gone!

261
00:20:51.230 --> 00:20:55.230
Even the sea clouds were obliterated!

262
00:21:01.240 --> 00:21:03.120
What a wonderful sight!

263
00:21:03.870 --> 00:21:06.450
This is how the sky should be!

264
00:21:11.370 --> 00:21:14.630
Wh-What was that explosion?!

265
00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:19.670
Thunderbolts are still
falling like rain too!

266
00:21:19.670 --> 00:21:22.590
I get the feeling
I won't be leaving alive!

267
00:21:23.050 --> 00:21:27.850
He eradicated Angel Island...

268
00:21:30.350 --> 00:21:32.270
How can you...

269
00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:36.440
How can you be so ruthless, Enel?!

270
00:21:40.860 --> 00:21:42.660
What a loud rumbling...

271
00:21:44.660 --> 00:21:45.830
We have to wait.

272
00:21:46.540 --> 00:21:49.500
We have to lead them
back to the Blue Sea!

273
00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:53.540
Luffy! Get on so we
can go back down!

274
00:21:54.170 --> 00:21:56.000
Everyone's headed for the Merry!

275
00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:58.000
We gotta get going, too!

276
00:21:58.760 --> 00:21:59.710
I can't.

277
00:22:00.170 --> 00:22:03.260
You can't? Why not?!
What're you talking about?!

278
00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:05.600
Even if you don't
need saving anymore...

279
00:22:06.100 --> 00:22:08.720
I still have unfinished business here!

280
00:22:08.720 --> 00:22:11.850
"Unfinished"? What could you
possibly have left to do here?!

281
00:22:11.850 --> 00:22:13.900
Are you trying to get back at Enel?!

282
00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:16.980
There's a golden bell in the sky!

283
00:22:17.360 --> 00:22:20.490
A golden...?

284
00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:23.360
Your life is more important
than that! Just look around!

285
00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:26.320
Even if lightning doesn't hurt you,

286
00:22:26.320 --> 00:22:30.410
Enel has the power to destroy
everything else around you!

287
00:22:30.410 --> 00:22:33.790
If you really want some gold,
just look at your arm!

288
00:22:34.370 --> 00:22:36.460
Forget about some golden bell!

289
00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:38.300
You're gonna get killed!

290
00:22:38.300 --> 00:22:40.090
I won't die...

291
00:22:40.090 --> 00:22:41.920
Will you quit it, already?! You–

292
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:43.260
You saw it yourself!

293
00:22:44.760 --> 00:22:46.180
Saw what?

294
00:22:50.970 --> 00:22:54.520
The City of Gold... It's really real!

295
00:22:59.570 --> 00:23:01.110
He wasn't lying!

296
00:23:03.150 --> 00:23:05.200
Chestnut head's ancestor...

297
00:23:08.030 --> 00:23:09.950
If it's there, that's fine.

298
00:23:09.950 --> 00:23:12.290
If it's not there, that's fine, too.

299
00:23:12.290 --> 00:23:15.790
It's not that I want
to prove his innocence.

300
00:23:16.750 --> 00:23:22.090
This is a duel with the man
who screwed up my life.

301
00:23:23.130 --> 00:23:25.630
He was telling the truth.

302
00:23:26.680 --> 00:23:30.100
So I have to let chestnut head
and the others below know...

303
00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:35.270
that the City of Gold is in the sky!

304
00:23:38.980 --> 00:23:40.900
If I ring that bell...

305
00:23:42.030 --> 00:23:43.780
they should be able to hear it!

306
00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:49.490
Otherwise, they'll keep on searching
the ocean floor until they die!

307
00:23:54.370 --> 00:23:55.460
Luffy...

308
00:23:56.580 --> 00:23:59.040
I can't let Enel take it!

309
00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:04.010
I'm sure a bell that big can
be heard from anywhere...

310
00:24:06.050 --> 00:24:10.220
so that's why I'm gonna
ring that golden bell!

311
00:24:14.060 --> 00:24:18.690
There's a huge bell
in the City of Gold, right?

312
00:24:19.190 --> 00:24:24.400
Yes, Noland's logbook
made mention of one.

313
00:24:24.780 --> 00:24:26.280
Why do you ask?

314
00:24:26.280 --> 00:24:27.860
Yeah, why?

315
00:24:29.550 --> 00:24:32.990
I just came up with a good idea!

316
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:34.580
What? What is it?!

317
00:24:35.370 --> 00:24:38.620
If we rang that huge bell...

318
00:24:38.620 --> 00:24:42.880
do you think chestnut head and
the monkeys below would hear it?

319
00:24:45.590 --> 00:24:47.970
They totally would, right?

320
00:24:50.390 --> 00:24:53.300
When he says he's gonna
do something, he means it.

321
00:24:53.640 --> 00:24:56.020
Then, he's...

322
00:24:56.350 --> 00:24:58.230
He did say that.

323
00:24:58.230 --> 00:25:00.350
But given the situation...

324
00:25:03.940 --> 00:25:05.280
The bell...

325
00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:07.780
He's really going to ring it?!

326
00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:12.990
Yeah. Even if Nami tries
to bring him back, he won't come.

327
00:25:14.030 --> 00:25:17.950
Because he and Enel
are after the same thing.

328
00:25:27.590 --> 00:25:28.380
I did it!

329
00:25:32.930 --> 00:25:36.010
Who gave you permission
to board this ship?

330
00:25:36.510 --> 00:25:37.600
Enel!

331
00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:50.110
Luffy! I told you it was a bad idea!

332
00:25:50.740 --> 00:25:51.820
Screw him!

333
00:25:53.320 --> 00:25:54.820
Well?

334
00:25:54.820 --> 00:25:58.580
Did you see that silly little
island vanish from the sky?

335
00:25:59.290 --> 00:26:00.660
You, girl.

336
00:26:00.660 --> 00:26:05.040
Can I assume you no longer
want to try and sweet-talk me

337
00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:07.250
into taking you to
the Endless Vearth again?

338
00:26:07.630 --> 00:26:08.460
Hell no!

339
00:26:08.460 --> 00:26:12.590
Once I have what I want,

340
00:26:12.590 --> 00:26:18.010
I will destroy all of Skypiea
with my next Raigo!

341
00:26:18.010 --> 00:26:21.560
No one will be allowed to escape now!

342
00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:30.150
Not even the handful of
voices directly below you!

343
00:26:30.690 --> 00:26:31.950
Directly below?!

344
00:26:32.570 --> 00:26:36.160
I will eradicate the land
unsuited for this sky,

345
00:26:37.030 --> 00:26:40.700
and return everything
to its rightful order!

346
00:26:41.370 --> 00:26:42.870
That is...

347
00:26:42.870 --> 00:26:47.000
That is my duty as God!

348
00:26:53.720 --> 00:26:55.680
As if I'd let you...

349
00:26:56.720 --> 00:27:00.890
have your way!

350
00:27:08.270 --> 00:27:10.360
Farewell, rubber man!

351
00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:13.860
Just sit idly by and
wait for the end to come!

352
00:27:15.950 --> 00:27:16.490
Luffy!

353
00:27:23.960 --> 00:27:24.660
Luffy!

354
00:27:28.790 --> 00:27:33.300
No one... can stop me now.

355
00:27:37.390 --> 00:27:40.050
Dammit!

356
00:27:40.430 --> 00:27:44.810
Mark my words, you will be
soaring into the sky tomorrow!

357
00:27:51.730 --> 00:27:53.030
Luffy...

358
00:27:55.950 --> 00:27:58.450
I'm going to...

359
00:28:02.410 --> 00:28:08.120
ring that bell!
